node.accessibility_caption: Photo by TODAY on May 19, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'Covid-19 TODAY 451 new Covid-19 cases in Singapore, tally stands at 28,794'

node.text:
Singapore has confirmed 451 new cases of Covid-19, said the Ministry of Health on Tuesday (May 19).⁣
⁣
This brings the total number of cases here to 28,794.⁣
⁣
The vast majority of the new cases are work permit holders residing in foreign worker dormitories.⁣
⁣
1 case is a Singaporean/permanent resident.⁣
@tmy.ming not really considered dropping bcos 1 lab is down so they can’t process as much results as before
@nepenthesgabby isnt that for yesterday’s one? they didnt mentioned it today?? im not shre
@tmy.ming I think the lab is still down hahah
😈😈😈 so few cases only? tomorrow cases will be high again when labs open. 😈😈😈
We’ll get there, slowly but surely! 💪
